ical case studies in a comparative perspective, the volume zooms in on the historical context of the advanced imperial and late antique Mediterranean space (2nd-8th centuries CE).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aCities and towns, AncientzMediterranean RegionxReligious aspects. 4aMetropole. 4aReligionswandel. 4aSpätantike. 4aStädtewandel. 7aRELIGION / Antiquities & Archaeology.2bisacsh  aUrban religion.  alate antiquity.  areligious changes.  aurban transformations.1 aAndo, Clifford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlömer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChatterjee, Paroma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeppin, Hartmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLätzer-Lasar, Asuman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLätzer-Lasar, Asuman, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorgan, Teresa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaja, Rubina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubens Urciuoli, Emiliano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRüpke, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalzman, Michele Renee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteuernagel, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUrciuoli, Emiliano Rubens, eeditor.4edt4http: